                <li class="option"><input type="radio" name="q1" value="b"> b) Internet Operating Telnet</li>
                <li class="option"><input type="radio" name="q1" value="c"> c) Internet Office Telephone</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="question" id="questiontwo">
            <h2>Question 2: John wants to use a creative commons licensed image for his website. Is this OK?</h2>
            <ul class="options">
                <li class="option"><input type="radio" name="q2" value="a"> a) Yes, if he doesn't make money</li>
                <li class="option"><input type="radio" name="q2" value="b"> b) Yes, for any case</li>
                <li class="option"><input type="radio" name="q2" value="c"> c) No, not in any case</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="question" id="questionthree">
            <h2>Question 3: Tiana wants to use a character from a book that's 200 years old for her Tik Tok. Is this OK?</h2>
            <ul class="options">
                <li class="option"><input type="radio" name="q3" value="a"> a) Yes, so long as it's in the public domain </li>
                <li class="option"><input type="radio" name="q3" value="b"> b) Yes, so long as she doesn't make money</li>
                <li class="option"><input type="radio" name="q3" value="c"> c) No, it is copyrighted</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <button onclick="submitQuiz()">Submit Answers</button>

        <canvas id="quizChart"></canvas>
    </div>

</body>

